# Code Comment Requirements

- Add a short `//` comment directly above every class you create or modify.
- Add a short `//` comment directly above every method/function you create or modify.
- In frontend scripts, also add `//` comments above object-literal methods (for example Alpine component methods in `wwwroot` pages).
- Comments should explain purpose and usage context (`what` and `when/why`) in plain language.
- Prefer concise comments (usually one line) and avoid boilerplate wording.
- Do not use XML-doc comments for this rule unless explicitly requested by the user.
- When touching existing code, backfill missing class/method `//` comments in the edited region.

## Examples

```csharp
// Resolves repo metadata and keeps a short-lived in-memory cache.
public class ModRepoService
{
    // Returns cached data, refreshing from remote source when stale.
    public async Task<ModRepoData> GetDataAsync(bool forceRefresh = false) { ... }
}
```
